body:
The following code fails to compile:
```
// test.sv

module dut #(
    parameter int unsigned Width = 32,
    localparam type T =
        struct packed {                                
            struct packed {
              logic [Width-1:0] field_a;
              logic             field_b;
            }     q;
            logic q_valid;
            logic p_ready;
        }
) (
    input T req_i,
    output T req_o
);

    assign req_o = req_i;

endmodule
```
with the following error:
```
%Error: Internal Error: test.sv:10:19: ../V3Width.cpp:8413: iterateEditMoveDTypep didn't get width resolution of DEFIMPLICITDTYPE '__typeimpsu1'
                                      : ... note: In instance 'dut'
   10 |             }     q;
      |                   ^
```
Note, non-nested structs in type parameter definitions seem to work fine.

I tested this with:
```
verilator --binary test.sv
```
within the latest Docker container (Verilator 5.042 2025-11-02).

QuestaSim can successfully elaborate this code. I checked the formal syntax section of the SystemVerilog LRM and it seems to be indeed legal syntax.

